content.detailedDescription: It was a winter night in november of 1999. myself and four other people were traveling to salcha alaska to stay the weekend in a friends cabin. we were just passing eileson air force base when i noticed a light. i said to my friends, when did they put up that tower. when we got closer i noticed three white lights. this is when we pulled to the side of the road. we noticed the three white lights about two hundred feet apart forming a triangle. in between the lights was an outline of a black craft. it was a dull matte black blocking out the stars in the night sky. the craft was hovering just above the spruce trees. black spuce in alaska do not grow very tall so i would estimate it being about fifty feet off the ground. it was completely silent. we watched it for around four minutes until one of the passengers said, let's just leave them be. so we did. we drove off and continued on our way. we never even talked about it. like it was an everyday normal event. looking back i am amazed at how unfrightened we were. it was almost like we were sent away from the craft purposely. we even had a camera in the car and never even considered using it. were we controlled that night by an unknown force ?
content.summary: Large black triangle. hovering silent above treetops. very close to it

content.detailedDescription: Approx. 12:40 am on the night of august 19th 2015 i went out in my backyard to sky watch as i often do after work. i was in my lounge chair always looking for anything moving. airplanes, meteorites, satellites or whatever. i first noticed the "ufo" at approx. 12:50 am coming from the south at a high rate of speed heading north. it did not deviate in direction or speed.  it took me approx. one second to calculate what i was witnessing. first thing that i noticed was that it was traveling at a very fast speed. if i had to estimate it i would say around 2000 mph. plus. the second thing that i noticed was that it was triangular in shape. the third thing that i noticed was that it seemed to have one white light at each corner. i also noticed that it seemed to be somewhat transparent. it was at a pretty high altitude, not sure how high as i had nothing to compare it to. i really can't say how big it was due to not knowing what altitude that it was. i have worked at our local airport in the maintenance dept. for the last 7 plus years. i know what an airplane flying through the sky looks like. this was not an airplane! as i watched it cross the sky i remember thinking... this is something that i can't explain. this is a triangle ufo. shortly after it disappeared out of sight i remember thinking wow, that is the triangular shaped ufo that a lot of people see. i then thought, who or what was piloting this craft?
content.summary: I observed it going from s. to n. very fast moving semi transparent, white light on all three corners. approx 6 seconds viewed.

content.detailedDescription:
Kentucky lake experience
11-24-10

one summer in the year 1958 to maybe 1959 my brother and i were headed on a camping, fishing trip on kentucky lake. my age would have been around 14 to 15 years at the time.  we packed our 16â€™ aluminum fishing boat with two motors (10hp & 71/2 hp johnsons), all the gas tanks (i think we had 3 tanks) we had and a cooler with bacon and egg, sandwich makings/hot dogs and drinks. we planned on traveling by boat to areas of the lake that were new to us. we were going to explore new areas, look for fossils and indian fire pits, and fish. our fishing boat was relatively slow by todayâ€™s standards and at the late afternoon of the first day we had gone up the tn river and reached a very small bay upstream and north of the leatherwood creek areas of the lake and fished there. we thought about spending the night there but the shore was too narrow to provide a good camping area. we moved on to leatherwood creek which is a big bay. we fished a bit in leatherwood creek bay and decided to make camp early since we were not familiar with the area. we made camp in the bay on the south side of leatherwood creek. there was a steep cliff behind us and we used the back drop of the cliff as a fire backstop. we made dinner early, gathered firewood, spread out our sleeping bags and decided to go to bed early and shortly after sunset since our flashlights were not that good in those days. in the 50-60â€™s the entire shore of the lake was wild and not inhabited with any fishing camps or cabins. the only two docks where we could get gas were antioch and buchanan and they were very little docks with one gas pump.  in fact, in those days we rarely saw another fishing boat on the lake and we took our baths in the lake. so, going to bed early was the only option for us. we got in our sleeping bags but shortly after, for some reason, we decided to take the boat out and try night fishing. we built the fire up quite big so we could see it from the lake to ensure we could get back to camp. we fished a short time and decided to get back to shore because a fog was coming in and we were afraid we might not get back to our camp if the fog obscured our view of the camp fire. when we got back to camp, i was glad we built up the fire as it was burned down quite low. after getting back to shore and pulling the boat up on the bank, we saw a floating round light across the bay and floating along the tree line at the top of the hill. it was floating along the north side of leatherwood creek and moving from the east in a westward direction. it was a color like the sun, and about the size of a pea or my little finger nail from our distance perspective.  it was moving at a speed i would guess to be about 10 miles per hour and hovering just above tree tops and there was no sound at all. it floated along the ridge for probably several hundred yards and then went over the hill and out of sight only to reappear a couple hundred yards farther away to our left. finally it floated out of sight. we went to bed and slept well. 

the funny thing was that while the 60â€™s were the age of the very popular and plentiful flying saucer and alien invasion movies, we should have been quite afraid of what we saw, but we were not. as example, on another time we returned to the cabin late in the evening from a movie in town. on the gravel county road near the cabin, we saw a huge glowing mound in the woods. to our imaginations it appeared to be a crashed ufo but on a closer look it was the embers left from a brush pile fire. i remember at first not knowing what it was and being afraid that it was a crashed ufo or something like the meteors from the war of the worlds movie. so, why in this case we had fear of what we saw but in the orb of leatherwood creek, we were not? what accounts for the difference?

that weekend our father came to the cabin from memphis where he worked. we told him our story and told him we thought it was a â€œwill-o'-the-wispâ€ (see wikipedia below). he said that it probably was and that he saw one as a young boy. dad said it was a ball of light that floated in through his bedroom window, floated down the hall and went out through the screen of the screen door. he went on to tell us that in the memphis news papers there had been a story that a big ufo had been seen over nashville that same week. if you were to draw a straight line along that ridge on leatherwood creek and extend it south east, it would run near nashville area. so, it is possible that we saw the same thing. it certainly was not any flying vehicle we know. if it were a helicopter with a spot light on it, it would not have appeared as a ball of light unless the spot light was pointing directly at us the entire length of its movements and we would have heard the rotors. so, we can rule out a chopper. 

this summer i went to leatherwood creek and found the cove where we camped. looking across the bay i covered an object about the size of a pea from that distance. it is the restaurant now there in the marina (which wasn't there in 59). the size of the restaurant is probably 100â€™ in length, so the yellow/white sphere we saw must have been about 100â€™ in diameter and likely more as it was higher up the hill than the marina. most all reports of â€œwill-oâ€™-the-wispâ€ are of small orbs of light the largest the size of a manâ€™s head. this light was much larger than that, so it is unlikely it was a will-0-the-wisp. what it was, i donâ€™t knowâ€¦weâ€™ll just say an unexplained large, slow moving ball of light out in the boonies and seen in the late 50â€™s.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Ball of light over kentucky lake that slowly moved down to  the shore and then out of sight

content.detailedDescription: On the night of last july 30 a green bright craft the size of a commercial jet flew for approximately two hours over three countries in south america, argentina, uruguay and brazil,  covering a distance of approximately 3400 km (2125 miles). it was witnessed by hundreds of people. dozens of videos were posted on youtube. media tried to suppress the real measure of the event, giving false explanations to the phenomenon and in a hastily manner. authorities involved are completely silent. i was at home at the time teaching english. i received an email from a friend on the next morning with a link to a news report about the case. at a first glance it really appeared to be a meteor, but it didn't take too long to notice that the press was hiding something due to the vast area where the object had been seen. it flew at variable speeds and altitudes over 3 countries in several directions. i had the feeling i should do something about it, and i did. i have prepared and stored in dropbox a 25 page very detailed report. it contains pictures, 32 videos, several calculations, proving that it was an intelligently controlled craft. please contact me, i suspect you will appreciate seeing my report published in your monthly journal.
content.region: State of Rio Grande do Sul
content.summary: The event took place over argentina, uruguay and brazil
content.locationName: Porto Alegre, State of Rio Grande do Sul

content.detailedDescription:
The time was around 10:30 pm when me and my two kids went outside to put up the goats and chickens for the night. the kids westen 21 and holly 22 are in the goat barn locking them up and i was walking around the barn/coop checking for strays when i came around the barn/coop i noticed it was suddenly vary bright out. i looked up facing west there was a vary bright light that was turning on and off randomly i told the kids to take a look at this and i asked them what do they think it was they did not know either but we all were amazed seeing the object/light. i told them this thing is strange as it would get vary bright and then dim some then get bright again and some times turn off. i told them to keep an eye on the object and that i was going to the house to get my cell phone to take some pics of it. i ran to the house and got the phone and when i came out the object was gone i asked them what happened and they just said it was gone and as i was standing there looking for it the light came back on but it was in a different location. it did all of the same things as before that is when i took a couple of pics of it and watched it for a while then it was gone again. i sat down and looked for it to show up again and it did this time in a new location. i took a few more pics of it and then i tried to record it with my phone but it just would not  show up on the recording but it did show up in the pics i took. we watched it for a few more minutes and then it was gone and did not come back.The next night we had two helicopters going around in circles at about the same time we seen the object the night before. the front helicopter did not have any lights on at all no strobes or anything which i thought was strange and it was a larger helicopter. the other was a smaller one and it did have the strobe flashing on the bottom of it. it looked as if they were searching for something or following something.
about a week later the helicopters came back around the same time 10:30 pm and the did the same thing as before.I could not figure out why on lights on them.
content.summary: Orb / ufo moving from first point seen to the north then vanished.

content.detailedDescription:
while hanging out with my girlfriend at my family home, a buddy of mine stops by and we all decide to walk to the deli for a six-pack. it had been a hot sunny sat. afternoon and the sun was going down. we would always cut across the local school field and did that evening. night had just fallen and as we were passing the backstop of the ball field i noticed a plane approach from e/ne. this was a common flight path for jets going southwest to jfk, so i glanced, but...It caught my eye because it moved slowly like a jet at a far distance yet was as low as a cesna type single engine private plane which we were used to because of deer park airport being blocks away. i did a double take because it was so slow and low it would have fallen into pilgrim state woods, and it made no sound. i said,"look at that!"
  a round disc craft with multi-colored lights flashing in a circular but erratic manner comes right toward us. it reminded me of the saucers in "the invaders" tv show of the sixties; lights revolving on the bottom outer edge. this was erratically flashing; hypnotically. we all felt that it was a self-aware machine; we could feel it looking at us. it was so close to us i later told others i could have hit it with a wrist-rocket(illegal slingshot)but not with a rock by hand; approx.200 ft. while passing directly overhead it turned a bright blue light on us. we felt it 'awarely' scan us with an intense static charge;our hair stood on end and the smell of electricity was powerful(reminded me of my h o train set when a boy). it scanned my thoughts and being, not just our bodies! i remember looking at frankie's hair standing up. the next thing i knew it was moving away or had it never slowed over us i don't know; strangely disorienting for all of us i later learned.
  "what was that?!" i exclaimed. frankie calmly says "the gardeners" and points toward the neighborhood sky which was filled with about 7-9 more moving in a grid pattern(monitoring/mapping?)over the town. he had just read "the hermit'by lobsang rampa which explained the phenomena for him and defined them thus. he's amazed but calm, i'm excited, and susan was terrified. she cried and wanted to go home. we never got our beer.
content.summary: saucer with rotating multiple lights floats over comac rd and over schoolyard that friends and i are cutting through and scans us with blue beam right over heads

content.detailedDescription: Gardner kansas,  taking dog out before bedtime.  i always look up having worked in aviation.  thought it was an air craft at first.  object flew straight line not wavering not blinking.  feelings were, just another a\c.  noticed it did not blink and as it was going away the lights did not change.  i did not feel other than normal. i did began to feel excited when i realised it was not acting normal for air craft.  i live next to an air port and am used to seeing a\c.  the object simply went out about 30 degrees from se horizen.
content.summary: Solid white light, none blinking, no color change of light from start to finish

content.detailedDescription: I was getting off the bus coming from work. as i was walking away from the bus stop i notice this bright light in the sky. first i thought it was a star but when i saw it moving a little i then thought it was an airplane, but there were no blinking lights like airplanes are suppose to have on them and it was moving too slow to be a plane. what made me realize that this was no ordinary craft was when it started slowly moving up and down. ascending and descending. then a second one appeared out of no where like it uncloaked itself. this one was much smaller. it darted to the left, stopped and then disappeared. the larger one that looked like venus slowing faded away. it was very interesting. a strange feeling came over me while i was seeing these objects. the feeling i got from these objects was like a message saying, "hello! can you see us." they wanted to be seen. i wish i had a video camera at the time. i'm sorry i was not able to catch it on video or take any pictures, but i just had to report it any way. i just had this need to tell someone.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: I thought it was seeing venus or jupiter until it started moving slowly up and down.

content.detailedDescription:
We were in a ferryboat from woodshold ma to marthas vineyard taking pictures of the shore on 5/23/15,at aprox. 10 am.  we did not realize that some of the photos contain something not usual up to now.

first picture contains a rare small cloud in a perfect clear dry morning of may.  no other clouds in the whole sky that morning
getting the photo to my pc and zooming to maximum we discover something dark over the cloud with a distortion of the atmosphere all around the cloud.

second picture of the shore, 10 min later, contains a round object seen on the left side over the small cliff, suspended on the sky.

as an institution you have more precise ways to confirm if the supposed objects are real, i would like to know if we really have a ufo in our pictures.

thank you, you are doing a tremendous effort to discover the truth.

pedro
content.summary: Sight

content.detailedDescription: On tuesday, august 18th of this year, i saw a large object while driving northwards on the interstate to my 10 o'clock flying over a mountain to the north end of tremonton, utah. the object was shaped very similar to a paraglider, although the object had nothing dangling beneath, nor did it have the actual cells of a paraglider. it was a very very dark grey in color. the two most frightening, or interesting features of this object were its size, it was at least 500 yards from tip tip, and 200 from stern to aft, the second, most striking feature was that it would fade into invisibility, to full visibility, and did so repeatedly, all while in its constant doing its constant figure 8 parallel to the surface of the mountain. it did so until the object remained invisible, and didn't come back. the ordeal lasted several minutes.
content.summary: Saw object apparently effortlessly float back and forth over a small mountain
